author: rwhitcomb
msg: One more modification to the comparator in TerraFileBrowserSkin:
make separate comparators for each column and direction so that
the inner compare loop isn't checking the column name for every
compare.  Also use File.compareTo because empirically it seems
faster than doing a "getName" and comparing the strings, plus
it respects the case-sensitivity of the operating system which
seems better for *nix.  The overall result seems to be a *little*
faster than before.  Testing shows that if there is NO comparator
then Arrays.sort is orders of magnitude faster than with one
(probably has to do with JIT compiling).
